HEADWORD: Terre-tenant
<hw>Terre"-ten`ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>terre</ets> earth, land + <ets>tenant</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>tenir</ets> to hold.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who has the
actual possession of land; the occupant.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>ter-tenant</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

